**Privacy Policy**
Effective Date: 7/7/2023
Tiluf built the Tiluf app as a Commercial app. This SERVICE is provided by Tiluf and is intended for use as is.
This Privacy Policy describes how Tiluf ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use the Tiluf App. By using the App, you agree to the terms and conditions of this Privacy Policy.
**Information We Collect**
We may collect the following information from users of the App:
1. **Location Permission (MANDATORY):** We require access to your device's location to facilitate the discovery of nearby people and showcase your AR status so that others can discover you. We may use location information even when the App is running in the background to increase the chance of getting discovered by others.
2. **Camera Permission (MANDATORY):** The App is a camera-based AR application, and camera access is necessary for the entire AR experience.
3. **Contact List Access:** We may request access to your contact list to enhance your socializing capabilities and help you forge meaningful connections with people in your proximity.
4. **File Access:** In order to post photos in AR, we may request access to your device's gallery or file storage.
**Use of Information**
We use the collected information to provide, maintain, and improve the functionality of the App, as well as to enhance your user experience. The information may be used for the following purposes:
1. **Location Information:** We use location information to enable features such as discovering nearby people and showcasing AR status. This information may be used when the App is running in the background.
2. **Camera Access:** Camera access is essential for the AR experience provided by the App.
3. **Contact List Access:** If you grant us access to your contact list, we may use this information to enhance socializing capabilities and facilitate connections with people in your proximity.
4. **File Access:** If you provide us with access to your device's gallery or file storage, we may use the content you select to enable photo posting in AR.
**Third-Party Services**
The App may use third-party services that collect information used to identify you. These services have their own privacy policies, and we recommend reviewing their policies for more information. The following third-party service providers may be used by the App:
- Google Play Services: (https://www.google.com/policies/privacy/)
- Google Analytics for Firebase: [(https://firebase.google.com/policies/analytics)
**Security**
We take commercially acceptable measures to protect the personal information you provide. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is completely secure and reliable. We cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information.
**Links to Other Sites**
The App may contain links to external websites that are not operated by us. We have no control over the content, privacy policies, or practices of these third-party sites. Therefore, we recommend that you review the privacy policies of these websites when you visit them.
**Children's Privacy**
The App is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided personal information, please contact us so that we can take the necessary actions to delete the information.
**Changes to this Privacy Policy**
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes to this policy will be effective when we post the revised Privacy Policy in the App. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.
**Contact Us**
If you have any questions or suggestions regarding this Privacy Policy, or want to get any of your data deleted then please contact us at mail@tiluf.com
